[2
Date: Fri, 12 Feb 1999 10:05:19 +0100
From: "L'age-Stehr, Johanna" <Lage-StehrJ@rki.de>
Subject: Yellow fever in Bolivia

The Robert Koch Institut, the German Yellow Fever vaccine producer, had
several requests this week from German doctors living in Santa Cruz, Bolivia
for supplies of vaccine for their own use in an outbreak of Yellow Fever.
Apparently the Bolivian newspaper "La Razon" had an article on 29 Jan
[1999 reporting an outbreak with 13 deaths and 20 "infected". The Bolivian
Embassy in Berlin has provided us with a copy of that article and an E-mail
address of "La Razon":
http://208.143.241.66/cuerpoe/edicion.htm
I have just requested more information [from them.
--
